Women Fixers Tackle Electronics (And Electronic Waste)

How comfortable are we with fixing our own stuff? The Restarters Project creates spaces for women and non-binary people to learn how to repair their own electronics. With billions of electronic waste being created every year, learning how to repair something, rather than buying something new, is a way to fight this problem.
